Title: The Short- and Long-Term Career Effects of Graduating in a Recession
Data Comments: Our data combines three administrative datasets from Statistics Canada. The first is the University Student Information System (USIS), which includes enrollment and graduate information of post-secondary students in Canada from 1974 to 1997. We augment the USIS data by linking it to income data from the T1 Family File (T1FF) between 1982 and 1999, and to an employer-employee matched dataset called the Longitudinal Employment Analysis Program database (LEAP).
